Absolutely the worst Chinese food in my 20 years in NYC.  I took a chance and it was a terrible decision.  It was honestly slimy, undercooked, flavorless, and all around terrible.  The only upside was that it was delivered quickly.  Having said that, you could get something tastier from the garbage can on the corner, so that would equate to delivery even faster than their already speedy service.  AVOID AT ALL COSTS.  Also, when I called to complain, I was sent to "managers" with decreasing fluency in English (which is obviously a ploy to disregard complaints) so I wasted $50 and everything ended up in the trash can.  Good luck guys - not the way to win customers...
